Dave,

Thanks for your assistance.

When I run the .pyw in IDLE there is no error given.  Likewise, if I 
cut and paste the whole command in a DOS window, it appears to 
execute without an error.

I did download the 1.5.5r4 source and built the files and the .msi 
installer.  Unfortunately, I still get the same errors.

----Mark


--- In cantera@yahoogroups.com, David Goodwin <dgoodwin@c...> wrote:
> Mark,
> 
> I suspect the problem is that the Cantera Python extension module 
was 
> built to link to one version of the Python DLL, and can't be used 
with 
> a different version.  Try running the temporary Python file that 
> ct2ctml creates, and see what error message it gives you.  If this 
is 
> the problem, you can build it from the source with whatever Python 
> version you like.
> 
> Dave
> 
>
